description: A club of man of letters and penniless artists that gathers at Pfaff’s, a beerhouse in Manhattan, is targeted by a demon from the Black Dimension— Varkendal, the soul collector. Our story is set in the 1850s, when young writer Willy North, fan of the late Edgar Allan Poe, finds in a Seneca Village junk shop a mysterious black mirror where a strange djinn – a “genie of the mirror” – is said to live. After North’s suicide, the artifact comes into the possession of Fitz-James O’Brien, Irish adventurer and writer of fantastic stories, and then falls into the hands of each of the members of the club, all of them encountering an untimely death... The only one who could save them is the person that the demon chose as a guide through the multiverse, the man who unwittingly guided him to the old Manhattan: Harlan Draka, the dampyr!
name: La stanza perduta

description: Among the ruins of the Seneca Village in Manhattan, P. T. Barnum, director of the "American Museum", and his loyal partner, General Tom Thumb, are on the verge of putting their hands on a unique creature: a vampire! Having lost his memory, Harlan Draka performs in the shows of the museum, using the new powers he got from the journey through the Black Dimension, and becomes friends with the other Barnum’s “artists”. While Caleb, Draka and his other friends are looking in vain for him in the multiverse, risking their lives against the Black Sentries, Dampyr, in the middle of the Civil War, will try to save old New York from the attack by Varkendal and the gangs allied with the Confederates, with the help of Barnum’s strange troops...
name: American Museum

description: Find out what Lex has in mind for Luthor Corps and Smallville in this next exciting installment!
name: Guardian Chapter 2

description: The curse of the nine hanged men’s dice... Klaus Druther never forgot the ominous words he heard the night when, still kids, he and his best friend Christian disobeyed their parents and entered the forest near Ruhewald, a spooky and terrifying place that Christian never came back from. What happened to the boy? Inside Klaus’ memory there’s a black hole filled with nightmares and ghosts... Stifling his fears and anxiety, many years later Klaus is back in Ruhewald. And he has a new friend, Harlan Draka. Together, they want to find the “inn of the last parties”, with its devilish owner, Waldo Zacharius...
name: La locanda delle ultime feste

description: Godwin Brumowski has a dream. He learned that one of his former comrade-in-arms is still alive. He could be a vampire, but he’s unbelievably able to sustain sunlight. The secret of a “healing” from vampirism is concealed in an old hidden temple on the peaks of Himalaya, where an unknown, well-disposed Master of the Night lives... Harlan, Tesla and Kurjak decide to meet him...
name: Il tempio sull'Himalaya

description: A writing in the snow... “Lisa loves Harlan"... drawn in blood! During his career, Dampyr faced every kind of dangers and creatures, but this is the endevour he’s most scared of, and at the same times he craves: meeting again Lisa, the girl with a double personality, enslaved by the flesh-eating demon Thorke. Which one is the real Lisa, now? The sweet and lonely toys seller or the crazed and dangerous serial killer? What is waiting for Harlan Draka in the enchanted village of Bruquewihr? Who is the Dark Man who kidnaps the chimney sweeps? And who’s the girl who takes them with her in the “Stork House”?
name: La casa delle cicogne

description: Bright Elegy is a Xeric Foundation Grant-winning love story. Not a romance, but a love story, a story in which time and memory and reality twist in a triple helix to form the life of the main character, James Sharpe. James runs away to an island in the Pacific northwest where he encounters Helen and is swept up in a quest to discover the truth about his past life and the death of his girlfriend. Bright Elegy tells the story of mystery, violence, and love - the story of one man's conflicted journey - a man trying to flee his past while at the same time sinking into childhood memories of succor and comfort.

A family-run ramen shop is home to good eats and bad manners! As the poster girl for her family's restaurant, Miki Onimaru has the best of intentions and the worst kind of social skills. Her hard demeanor and her queasy stomach keep business at bay, and while this attractive girl's looks might not quite kill, her special brand of martial arts certainly could!
name: Volume 1

description: Orphen is back in action, waving his wand and flaunting his skills, but his quick wit and vulgar mouth won't save him now! When Orphen finally catches up with Azalie, he'll have to face the shocking truth about the identity of his former flame!
name: Volume 2

description: Miki discovers that the ramen business isn't for the faint of heart, and she'll have to put her martial arts to good use to beat the competition! But while her scare tactics might work with local gang members and thugs, she'll have to kick it up a notch to win this war of the ramen shops!
name: Volume 2

description: Orphen is reunited with Leticia, a beautiful and gifted sorceress from his past. Their reunion is short-lived, however, as operatives from the Tower of Fang - convinced that Orphen has something that they desperately want - launch a series of deadly attacks. Orphen makes short work of his enemies, but little does he know that from the shadows an old and familiar foe has set plans of her own in motion...
name: Volume 4

description: The sorcerer Orphen is on a magic-for-hire-mission, and along with his wand-wielding understudy and bone-headed companion, he must retrieve a magical ring from the mansion of a beautiful young woman. This should be no sweat for the seasoned sorcerer, but a sweet-tempered maid with an interest in the black arts will complicate an already sticky situation.
name: Volume 1

description:
Orphen receives a nocturnal visit from a most unwelcome visitor - a ghost! Ethereal entities are the least of Orhpen's worries, though, as hired assassins and ghastly snake men appear, hungry for blood.

It's going to take a little help from the curvaceous Hirietta to provide some answers, but Orphen might not like what he finds when a trip to a ruined mansion brings him face-to-face with a powerful yet familiar evil...
name: Volume 3

description: With Daredevil Gone From Hell's Kitchen, The Hand's New Leader Makes His Move For Ultimate Power. But Why Is Wilson Fisk Targeting Wakandan Citizens, And Can T'Challa Save The One Woman Who Holds The Key To Unlocking The Kingpin's Plans? And When The Deadly Lady Bullseye And Typhoid Mary Take Aim, It's Time For The Panther To Call In Allies Of His Own: Falcon And Luke Cage! Ever Since T'challa Agreed To Take Over For DD, You Knew This War Was Coming. Now, Here It Is! The Former King Of Wakanda And The Former Kingpin Of Crime Wage War In A Deadly Game, With The Panther's Homeland As The Prize!
